body:
Would replacing the following code added in 6b475bdb78eb671866419ff84a4cda6285c90244 in lib/config/config.go be consistent with the intent of the untrusted feature and likely to fix the problem? 
```
if dev.EncryptionPassword != "" {
			// There's a password set, no check required
			continue
		}
```
Add OR:
```
if dev.EncryptionPassword != "" || f.type == config.FolderTypeReceiveEncrypted {
			// There's a password set or the folder is received encrypted, no check required
			continue
		}
```
The syntax and other aspects may not be correct (I don't know go or the syncthing code structure), but it seems like an untrusted device share is acceptable if a password is set OR the folder is a receive encrypted type (where you shouldn't know the password).
